ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIB.name: ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIB

revisions.description: Added the following enumerations for object cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol - allProtocols(14) Updated the description of cshcProtocolFibTcamTotal and cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalTotal.

Added following OBJECT-GROUP - cshcProtocolFibTcamWidthTypeGroup Added the following enumerations for object cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol - mplsVpn(11) - fcMpls(12) - ipv6LocalLink(13) Added new compliance - ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIBCompliance3

Added following OBJECT-GROUP - cshcNetflowFlowResourceUsageGroup - cshcMacUsageExtGroup - cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageExtGroup - cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageGroup - cshcQosResourceUsageGroup - cshcModTopDropIfIndexListGroup - cshcMetResourceUsageGroup Added the following enumerations for object cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol - l2VpnPeer(7) - l2VpnIpv4Multicast(8) - l2VpnIpv6Multicast(9) Added new compliance - ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIBCompliance2
Add the following new enumerations to cshcCPURateLimiterNetworkLayer: layer2Input(3) and layer2Output(4). Add cshcFibTcamUsageExtGroup.
Initial revision of this MIB module.

ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoSwitchHardwareCapacityMIB.description: This MIB module defines the managed objects for hardware capacity of Cisco switching devices. The hardware capacity information covers the following but not limited to features: forwarding, rate-limiter ... The following terms are used throughout the MIB: CAM: Content Addressable Memory. TCAM: Ternary Content Addressable Memory. FIB: Forwarding Information Base. VPN: Virtual Private Network. QoS: Quality of Service. CPU rate-limiter: Mechanism to rate-limit or restrict undesired traffic to the CPU. MPLS: Multiprotocol Label Switching.

CshcInternalChannelType.name: CshcInternalChannelType
CshcInternalChannelType.description: An enumerated value indicating the type of an internal channel. eobc - ethernet out-of-band channel. ibc - in-band channel.

cshcMacUsageTable.name: cshcMacUsageTable
cshcMacUsageTable.description: This table contains MAC table capacity for each switching engine, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB, capable of providing this information.

cshcMacUsageEntry.name: cshcMacUsageEntry
cshcMacUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for MAC table hardware capacity on a switching engine.

cshcMacCollisions.name: cshcMacCollisions
cshcMacCollisions.description: This object indicates the number of Ethernet frames whose source MAC address the switching engine failed to learn while constructing its MAC table.

cshcMacUsed.name: cshcMacUsed
cshcMacUsed.description: This object indicates the number of MAC table entries that are currently in use for this switching engine.

cshcMacTotal.name: cshcMacTotal
cshcMacTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of MAC table entries available for this switching engine.

cshcMacMcast.name: cshcMacMcast
cshcMacMcast.description: This object indicates the total number of multicast MAC table entries on this switching engine.

cshcMacUcast.name: cshcMacUcast
cshcMacUcast.description: This object indicates the total number of unicast MAC table entries on this switching engine.

cshcMacLines.name: cshcMacLines
cshcMacLines.description: This object indicates the total number of MAC table lines on this switching engine. The MAC table is organized as multiple MAC entries per line.

cshcMacLinesFull.name: cshcMacLinesFull
cshcMacLinesFull.description: This object indicates the total number of MAC table lines full on this switching engine. A line full means all the MAC entries on the line are occupied.

cshcVpnCamUsageTable.name: cshcVpnCamUsageTable
cshcVpnCamUsageTable.description: This table contains VPN CAM capacity for each entity, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB, capable of providing this information.

cshcVpnCamUsageEntry.name: cshcVpnCamUsageEntry
cshcVpnCamUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for VPN CAM hardware capacity on an entity.

cshcVpnCamUsed.name: cshcVpnCamUsed
cshcVpnCamUsed.description: This object indicates the number of VPN CAM entries that are currently in use.

cshcVpnCamTotal.name: cshcVpnCamTotal
cshcVpnCamTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of VPN CAM entries.

cshcFibTcamUsageTable.name: cshcFibTcamUsageTable
cshcFibTcamUsageTable.description: This table contains FIB TCAM capacity for each entity, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB, capable of providing this information.

cshcFibTcamUsageEntry.name: cshcFibTcamUsageEntry
cshcFibTcamUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for FIB TCAM hardware capacity on an entity.

cshc72bitsFibTcamUsed.name: cshc72bitsFibTcamUsed
cshc72bitsFibTcamUsed.description: This object indicates the number of 72 bits FIB TCAM entries that are currently in use.

cshc72bitsFibTcamTotal.name: cshc72bitsFibTcamTotal
cshc72bitsFibTcamTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of 72 bits FIB TCAM entries available.

cshc144bitsFibTcamUsed.name: cshc144bitsFibTcamUsed
cshc144bitsFibTcamUsed.description: This object indicates the number of 144 bits FIB TCAM entries that are currently in use.

cshc144bitsFibTcamTotal.name: cshc144bitsFibTcamTotal
cshc144bitsFibTcamTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of 144 bits FIB TCAM entries available.

cshc288bitsFibTcamUsed.name: cshc288bitsFibTcamUsed
cshc288bitsFibTcamUsed.description: This object indicates the number of 288 bits FIB TCAM entries that are currently in use.

cshc288bitsFibTcamTotal.name: cshc288bitsFibTcamTotal
cshc288bitsFibTcamTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of 288 bits FIB TCAM entries available.

cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageTable.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageTable
cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageTable.description: This table contains FIB TCAM usage per specified Layer 3 protocol on an entity capable of providing this information.

cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageEntry.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageEntry
cshcProtocolFibTcamUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for FIB TCAM usage for the specific Layer 3 protocol on an entity as specified by the entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol
cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol.description: This object indicates the Layer 3 protocol utilizing FIB TCAM resource. 'ipv4' - indicates Internet Protocol version 4. 'mpls' - indicates Multiprotocol Label Switching. 'eom' - indicates Ethernet over MPLS. 'ipv6' - indicates Internet Protocol version 6. 'ipv4Multicast' - indicates Internet Protocol version 4 for multicast traffic. 'ipv6Multicast' - indicates Internet Protocol version 6 for multicast traffic. 'l2VpnPeer' - indicates Layer 2 VPN Peer traffic. 'l2VpnIpv4Multicast' - indicates Internet Protocol version 4 for multicast traffic on Layer 2 VPN. 'l2VpnIpv6Multicast' - indicates Internet Protocol version 6 for multicast traffic on Layer 2 VPN. 'fcoe' - indicates Fibre Channel over Ethernet. 'mplsVpn' - indicates MPLS Layer 3 VPN aggregate labels. 'fcMpls' - indicates Fibre Channel over MPLS tunnels. 'ipv6LocalLink' - indicates Internet Protocol version 6 Local Link. 'allProtocols' - indicates all protocols within the entPhysicalIndex.

cshcProtocolFibTcamUsed.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamUsed
cshcProtocolFibTcamUsed.description: This object indicates the number of FIB TCAM entries that are currently in use for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol.

cshcProtocolFibTcamTotal.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamTotal
cshcProtocolFibTcamTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of FIB TCAM entries are currently allocated for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol. A value of zero indicates that the total number of FIB TCAM for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol is not available.

cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalUsed.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalUsed
cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalUsed.description: This object indicates the number of logical FIB TCAM entries that are currently in use for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol.

cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalTotal.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalTotal
cshcProtocolFibTcamLogicalTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of logical FIB TCAM entries that are currently allocated for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol. A value of zero indicates that the total number of logical FIB TCAM for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol is not available.

cshcProtocolFibTcamWidthType.name: cshcProtocolFibTcamWidthType
cshcProtocolFibTcamWidthType.description: This object indicates the entry width type for the protocol denoted by cshcProtocolFibTcamProtocol. 'singleWidth' - indicates each logical entry is using one physical entry. 'doubleWidth' - indicates each logical entry is using two physical entries. 'quadWidth' - indicates each logical entry is using four physical entries.

cshcAdjacencyUsageTable.name: cshcAdjacencyUsageTable
cshcAdjacencyUsageTable.description: This table contains adjacency capacity for each entity capable of providing this information.

cshcAdjacencyUsageEntry.name: cshcAdjacencyUsageEntry
cshcAdjacencyUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for adjacency hardware capacity on an entity, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcAdjacencyUsed.name: cshcAdjacencyUsed
cshcAdjacencyUsed.description: This object indicates the number of adjacency entries that are currently in use.

cshcAdjacencyTotal.name: cshcAdjacencyTotal
cshcAdjacencyTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of adjacency entries available.

cshcForwardingLoadTable.name: cshcForwardingLoadTable
cshcForwardingLoadTable.description: This table contains Layer 3 forwarding load information for each switching engine capable of providing this information.

cshcForwardingLoadEntry.name: cshcForwardingLoadEntry
cshcForwardingLoadEntry.description: Each row contains management information of Layer 3 forwarding load on a switching engine, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcForwardingLoadPktRate.name: cshcForwardingLoadPktRate
cshcForwardingLoadPktRate.description: This object indicates the forwarding rate of Layer 3 packets.

cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakRate.name: cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakRate
cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakRate.description: This object indicates the peak forwarding rate of Layer 3 packets.

cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakTime.name: cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakTime
cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakTime.description: This object describes the time when the peak forwarding rate of Layer 3 packets denoted by cshcForwardingLoadPktPeakRate occurs. This object will contain 0-1-1,00:00:00.0 if the peak time information is not available.

cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageTable.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageTable
cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageTable.description: This table contains adjacency capacity per resource type and its usage for each entity capable of providing this information.

cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageEntry.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageEntry
cshcAdjacencyResourceUsageEntry.description: Each row contains the management information for a particular adjacency resource and switch engine, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcAdjacencyResourceIndex.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceIndex
cshcAdjacencyResourceIndex.description: This object indicates a unique value that identifies an adjacency resource.

cshcAdjacencyResourceDescr.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceDescr
cshcAdjacencyResourceDescr.description: This object indicates a description of the adjacency resource.

cshcAdjacencyResourceUsed.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceUsed
cshcAdjacencyResourceUsed.description: This object indicates the number of adjacency entries that are currently in use.

cshcAdjacencyResourceTotal.name: cshcAdjacencyResourceTotal
cshcAdjacencyResourceTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of adjacency entries available.

cshcMetResourceUsageTable.name: cshcMetResourceUsageTable
cshcMetResourceUsageTable.description: This table contains information regarding Multicast Expansion Table (MET) resource usage and utilization for a switching engine capable of providing this information.

cshcMetResourceUsageEntry.name: cshcMetResourceUsageEntry
cshcMetResourceUsageEntry.description: Each row contains information of the usage and utilization for a particular MET resource and switching engine, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcMetResourceIndex.name: cshcMetResourceIndex
cshcMetResourceIndex.description: An arbitrary positive integer value that uniquely identifies a Met resource.

cshcMetResourceDescr.name: cshcMetResourceDescr
cshcMetResourceDescr.description: This object indicates a description of the MET resource.

cshcMetResourceUsed.name: cshcMetResourceUsed
cshcMetResourceUsed.description: This object indicates the number of MET entries used by this MET resource.

cshcMetResourceTotal.name: cshcMetResourceTotal
cshcMetResourceTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of MET entries available for this MET resource.

cshcMetResourceMcastGrp.name: cshcMetResourceMcastGrp
cshcMetResourceMcastGrp.description: This object indicates the number of the multicast group for this MET resource. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this MET feature.

cshcModuleInterfaceDropsTable.name: cshcModuleInterfaceDropsTable
cshcModuleInterfaceDropsTable.description: This table contains interface drops information on each module capable of providing this information.

cshcModuleInterfaceDropsEntry.name: cshcModuleInterfaceDropsEntry
cshcModuleInterfaceDropsEntry.description: Each row contains management information for dropped traffic on a specific module, identified by the entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB, and capable of providing this information.

cshcModTxTotalDroppedPackets.name: cshcModTxTotalDroppedPackets
cshcModTxTotalDroppedPackets.description: This object indicates the total dropped outbound packets on all physical interfaces of this module.

cshcModRxTotalDroppedPackets.name: cshcModRxTotalDroppedPackets
cshcModRxTotalDroppedPackets.description: This object indicates the total dropped inbound packets on all physical interfaces of this module.

cshcModTxTopDropPort.name: cshcModTxTopDropPort
cshcModTxTopDropPort.description: This object indicates the ifIndex value of the interface that has the largest number of total dropped outbound packets among all the physical interfaces on this module. If there were no dropped outbound packets on any physical interfaces of this module, this object has the value 0. If there are multiple physical interfaces of this module having the same largest number of total dropped outbound packets, the ifIndex of the first such interfaces will be assigned to this object.

cshcModRxTopDropPort.name: cshcModRxTopDropPort
cshcModRxTopDropPort.description: This object indicates the ifIndex value of the interface that has the largest number of total dropped inbound packets among all the physical interfaces of this module. If there were no dropped inbound packets on any physical interfaces of this module, this object has the value 0. If there are multiple physical interfaces of this module having the same largest number of total dropped inbound packets, the ifIndex of the first such interfaces will be assigned to this object.

cshcModTxTopDropIfIndexList.name: cshcModTxTopDropIfIndexList
cshcModTxTopDropIfIndexList.description: This object indicates the ifIndex values of the list of interfaces that have the largest number of total dropped outbound packets among all the physical interfaces of this module.

cshcModRxTopDropIfIndexList.name: cshcModRxTopDropIfIndexList
cshcModRxTopDropIfIndexList.description: This object indicates the ifIndex values of the list of interfaces that have the largest number of total dropped inbound packets among all the physical interfaces of this module.

cshcInterfaceBufferTable.name: cshcInterfaceBufferTable
cshcInterfaceBufferTable.description: This table contains buffer capacity information for each physical interface capable of providing this information.

cshcInterfaceBufferEntry.name: cshcInterfaceBufferEntry
cshcInterfaceBufferEntry.description: Each row contains buffer capacity information for a specific physical interface capable of providing this information.

cshcInterfaceTransmitBufferSize.name: cshcInterfaceTransmitBufferSize
cshcInterfaceTransmitBufferSize.description: The aggregate buffer size of all the transmit queues on this interface.

cshcInterfaceReceiveBufferSize.name: cshcInterfaceReceiveBufferSize
cshcInterfaceReceiveBufferSize.description: The aggregate buffer size of all the receive queues on this interface.

cshcInternalChannelTable.name: cshcInternalChannelTable
cshcInternalChannelTable.description: This table contains information for each internal channel interface on each physical entity, such as a module, capable of providing this information.

cshcInternalChannelEntry.name: cshcInternalChannelEntry
cshcInternalChannelEntry.description: Each row contains management information for an internal channel interface of a specific type on a specific physical entity, such as a module, identified by the entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB, and capable of providing this information.

cshcIntlChnlType.name: cshcIntlChnlType
cshcIntlChnlType.description: The type of this internal channel.

cshcIntlChnlRxPacketRate.name: cshcIntlChnlRxPacketRate
cshcIntlChnlRxPacketRate.description: Five minute exponentially-decayed moving average of inbound packet rate for this channel.

cshcIntlChnlRxTotalPackets.name: cshcIntlChnlRxTotalPackets
cshcIntlChnlRxTotalPackets.description: The total number of the inbound packets accounted for this channel.

cshcIntlChnlRxDroppedPackets.name: cshcIntlChnlRxDroppedPackets
cshcIntlChnlRxDroppedPackets.description: The number of dropped inbound packets for this channel.

cshcIntlChnlTxPacketRate.name: cshcIntlChnlTxPacketRate
cshcIntlChnlTxPacketRate.description: Five minute exponentially-decayed moving average of outbound packet rate for this channel.

cshcIntlChnlTxTotalPackets.name: cshcIntlChnlTxTotalPackets
cshcIntlChnlTxTotalPackets.description: The total number of the outbound packets accounted for this channel.

cshcIntlChnlTxDroppedPackets.name: cshcIntlChnlTxDroppedPackets
cshcIntlChnlTxDroppedPackets.description: The number of dropped outbound packets for this channel.

cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesTable.name: cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesTable
cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesTable.description: This table contains information regarding CPU rate limiters resources.

cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesEntry.name: cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesEntry
cshcCPURateLimiterResourcesEntry.description: Each row contains management information of CPU rate limiter resources for a managed network layer.

cshcCPURateLimiterNetworkLayer.name: cshcCPURateLimiterNetworkLayer
cshcCPURateLimiterNetworkLayer.description: This object indicates the network layer for which the CPU rate limiters are applied. 'layer2' - Layer 2. 'layer3' - Layer 3. 'layer2Input' - Ingress Layer 2. Applicable for devices which support CPU rate limiters on the Ingress Layer 2 traffic. 'layer2Output' - Egress Layer 2. Applicable for devices which support CPU rate limiters on the Egress Layer 2 traffic.

cshcCPURateLimiterTotal.name: cshcCPURateLimiterTotal
cshcCPURateLimiterTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of CPU rate limiters avaiable.

cshcCPURateLimiterUsed.name: cshcCPURateLimiterUsed
cshcCPURateLimiterUsed.description: This object indicates the number of CPU rate limiters that is currently in use.

cshcCPURateLimiterReserved.name: cshcCPURateLimiterReserved
cshcCPURateLimiterReserved.description: This object indicates the number of CPU rate limiters which is reserved by the switching device.

cshcIcamUtilizationTable.name: cshcIcamUtilizationTable
cshcIcamUtilizationTable.description: This table contains information regarding ICAM (Internal Content Addressable Memory) Resource usage and utilization for a switching engine capable of providing this information.

cshcIcamUtilizationEntry.name: cshcIcamUtilizationEntry

cshcIcamCreated.name: cshcIcamCreated

cshcIcamFailed.name: cshcIcamFailed

cshcIcamUtilization.name: cshcIcamUtilization

cshcNetflowFlowMaskTable.name: cshcNetflowFlowMaskTable

cshcNetflowResourceUsageIndex.description: An arbitrary positive integer value that uniquely identifies a Netflow resource.

cshcNetflowResourceUsageDescr.name: cshcNetflowResourceUsageDescr

cshcNetflowResourceUsageUtil.name: cshcNetflowResourceUsageUtil

cshcQosResourceUsageEntry.description: Each row contains management information for QoS capacity and its usage on an entity, as specified by entPhysicalIndex in ENTITY-MIB.

cshcQosResourceType.name: cshcQosResourceType
cshcQosResourceType.description: This object indicates the QoS resource type.

cshcQosResourceUsed.name: cshcQosResourceUsed
cshcQosResourceUsed.description: This object indicates the number of QoS entries that are currently in use.

cshcQosResourceTotal.name: cshcQosResourceTotal
cshcQosResourceTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of QoS entries available.
